From 2c6e58a75063622fb1e676cd08c7f04bbf4cfb95 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 21:21:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 3: Body compressor for density and pumping character

Adds a feed-forward peak compressor operating in the log domain on the
gain-reduction value, with exponentially smoothed attack/release. Inserted
on the distorted high band after post-EQ but before mixing back with the
clean sub, so the sub keeps its natural dynamics while the body gets the
"glued" pumping character commercial kicks rely on for perceived loudness.

Params:
- comp_threshold (-40..0 dB, default -6)
- comp_ratio (1..20, default 1.0 = bypass)
- comp_attack (0.1..50 ms, default 3)
- comp_release (5..500 ms, default 80)
- comp_makeup (0..18 dB, default 0)

All six presets tuned with characteristic compression: Sub Pressure gentle
2:1 with 10ms attack to preserve dynamics; Industrial brutal 10:1 with 1.5ms
attack and 50ms release for hard pumping; others land in between. UI grew
a COMP panel in row 3 next to PUNCH. Render path mirrors the same chain.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
